1. The IRS does not have a recording system in place for callers before they can get through to an agent.
2. The IRS lacks a mechanism to track and record the time callers spend waiting or on hold.
3. The IRS does not have a system to monitor the duration of calls before the caller reaches an agent.
4. There is no record of the time spent by discouraged callers who do not complete their calls.
5. The IRS does not have a way to track the time spent by callers who hang up before reaching an agent.
6. The IRS does not have a system to record the time spent by callers in the waiting queue.